Attempted to use the different configuration files recommended by [Boto documentation|http://boto.readthedocs.org/en/latest/boto_config_tut.html].  In my attempts, I added the following to the boto config file:
{code}
[Boto]
ca_certificates_file = system
{code}
{quote}
*ca_certificates_file*:
Location of CA certificates or the keyword “system”. Using the system keyword lets boto get out of the way and makes the SSL certificate validation the responsibility the underlying SSL implementation provided by the system.
{quote}
The issue still occurred.  I also tried adding the absolute path the HPE Helion Eucalyptus root certificate.  This also resulted in the same error.  Ultimately, I had to use 'localhost' (which doesn't use an HTTPS endpoint) instead of the region name of the cloud.
